nodes.title: Info
widgets_values:
================================
 JPS Workflow 2x Upscale - v2.0
================================

4 Generation Modes (blue nodes)
===============================

- TXT2IMG
- IMG2IMG
- Canny Control Net
- Depth Control Net

Strength and Ctrl-Options are not used by TXT2IMG.

Ctrl-Options are not uses by IMG2IMG.


Revision Mode (brown nodes)
=========================================

- ON/OFF Switch for Revision Mode
- Option to turn ON/OFF Positive/Negative TXT Prompts

All Options are only active if Revision Mode is turned ON. 


Image Adapter Mode (yellow nodes)
===============================================

- ON/OFF Switch

You can use up to 3 pictures for input, but usually you get better results with 1 or 2.

Results are best if you keep close to square aspect ratio. Extreme ratios like 21:9 or 9:21 don't work well.

Options are only active if the corresponding Image Adapter Mode is turned ON.


Additional Features
===================

- 2 variants (Base + Refiner / Base Only) with adjustable Refiner Percentage
- Upscaled versions of the 2 variants
- Styles Option
- Use resolution from settings or input image
- History view
- Clean layout with pipelines
- Disable parts of the workflow (for example upscaler)

You may disable parts of the workflow by cutting the wires between the nodes "Base", "B UP", "Refiner", "R UP". 

If you cut "Base" this will also disable the upscaled version "B UP" and if you cut "Refiner" you will also disable "R UP", because the upscaled versions need the lower resolution image as starting point.

You can switch between resolution from settings or input image. The resolution from input image will adjust the image to the closest recommended SDXL resolution.


Additional Info
===============

All required nodes should be available through ComfyUI Manager:

* ComfyUI Impact Pack
* Derfuu_ComfyUI_ModdedNodes
* WAS Node Suite
* SDXL Prompt Styler
* IPAdapter-ComfyUI
* (WIP) ComfyUI's ControlNet Auxiliary Preprocessors
* rgthree's ComfyUi Nodes
* JPS Custom Nodes for ComfyUI

It's recommended to change "Link Render Mode" to "Straight" or "Hidden" for a better user experience, if you don't want to edit the workflow. Cutting and connecting wires to turn on/off parts of the workflow still works with "Hidden", but you have to to it without visual feedback. The color of the dots still tell you if they are connected.

You have to change some nodes to your own filenames, when you first use this workflow.

"Seed" in Basic Setting is not used by this workflow. Use the better separate seed node instead.
